Porsha Dyanne Williams (born June 22, 1981), also known by her former married name Porsha Stewart, is an American television personality, model, actress and singer. Born and raised in Atlanta, Georgia, she modeled for music videos and calendar spreads in her early adulthood. In 2011, she came to prominence after marrying football player Kordell Stewart in an elaborate ceremony broadcast on the television series Platinum Weddings, although they experienced a widely publicized divorce in 2013. In 2012, Williams was cast in the fifth season of the reality television series The Real Housewives of Atlanta. In 2014, she launched a career in the music industry with the launch of her single "Flatline" under the record label Kandi Koated Entertainment. Williams was a contestant on the eighth installment of the reality competition series, The Celebrity Apprentice, now known as The New Celebrity Apprentice. She played for the charity "Hosea". On January 23, 2017, she was the eighth contestant fired, finishing in 8th place and raising no money for her charity.
